-- Crafts retailer Michaels makes lackluster market debut
-- 
-- Fri Jun 27, 2014 10:33AM EDT
-- None



June 27 (Reuters) - Shares of Michaels Cos Inc <MIK.O> fell as much as 2 percent in their return to the market, valuing the biggest U.S. arts and crafts retailer at about $3.4 billion.

The Irving, Texas-based company raised about $472.6 million after its offering of 27.8 million shares was priced at the low end of the expected $17-$19. [ID:nL2N0P729R] Michaels, which owns several brands such as Recollections, Artist's Loft and Loops & Threads, sold all the shares in the offering. The company's shares opened at $17 and touched a low of $16.70 on the Nasdaq on Friday.